"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VirtualMachineSpecification","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/virtualmachinespecification","abstract":[{"text":"The hardware specification for a virtual machine.","type":"text"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Versioning":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/versioning","title":"Versioning & Release Schedule","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Understand what version numbers mean and what to expect from each release.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Versioning","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/VirtualMachineState/error":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/virtualmachinestate\/error","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The VM encountered an error and stopped.","type":"text"}],"title":"VirtualMachineState.error","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineState\/error","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"error","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GitHubActionsGuide":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/githubactionsguide","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"text":"Run self-hosted macOS GitHub Actions runners in Spooktacular VMs with ephemeral isolation and automatic scaling.","type":"text"}],"title":"Configuring GitHub Actions Runners","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","kind":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/VirtualMachineBundle":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/virtualmachinebundle","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A virtual machine bundle stored on disk.","type":"text"}],"title":"VirtualMachineBundle","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineBundle","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VirtualMachineBundle","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VirtualMachineBundle","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/RemoteDesktop":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/remotedesktop","kind":"article","title":"Remote Desktop Access","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Connect to Spooktacular VMs via VNC for remote development, QA testing, and design review.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RemoteDesktop","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/CloneManager":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/clonemanager","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Creates copy-on-write clones of virtual machine bundles.","type":"text"}],"title":"CloneManager","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CloneManager","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CloneManager","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CloneManager","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/RestoreImageManager":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/restoreimagemanager","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Manages macOS restore images (IPSWs) for virtual machine installation.","type":"text"}],"title":"RestoreImageManager","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/RestoreImageManager","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"RestoreImageManager","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RestoreImageManager","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/OpenClawGuide":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/openclawguide","kind":"article","title":"Running OpenClaw in Virtual Machines","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Run two isolated OpenClaw AI agent instances on a single Mac — each with its own workspace, channels, and API keys.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/OpenClawGuide","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/JenkinsGuide":{"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/jenkinsguide","title":"Configuring Jenkins Nodes","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/JenkinsGuide","abstract":[{"text":"Run Jenkins build agents in Spooktacular VMs for iOS and macOS CI\/CD.","type":"text"}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/VirtualMachineState":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/virtualmachinestate","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The lifecycle state of a virtual machine.","type":"text"}],"title":"VirtualMachineState","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineState","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VirtualMachineState","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"VirtualMachineState","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/BlueBubblesGuide":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/bluebubblesguide","kind":"article","title":"Running BlueBubbles iMessage Server","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Set up a BlueBubbles iMessage server in a macOS VM — a dramatically simpler alternative to VMware on Windows.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/BlueBubblesGuide","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/GettingStarted":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted","kind":"article","title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GettingStarted","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/Compatibility":{"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Compatibility","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Compatibility","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/Compatibility","abstract":[{"text":"Checks version compatibility between the host macOS","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and a macOS restore image (IPSW).","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Compatibility","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/compatibility"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/CLIReference":{"url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/clireference","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"text":"Manage macOS virtual machines from the terminal with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"text":" CLI.","type":"text"}],"title":"Using the spook Command-Line Interface","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","kind":"article","type":"topic"}}}